'''Write a program in Python that reads two numbers on the keyboard and say which 
is the largest and which is the smallest'''
#getting two inputs to compare
first=input("tell me the first number to compare ")
second=input("tell me the second number to compare ")
#Comparing two numbers
if first>second:
    print(f"{first} is the biggest number")
elif second>first:
    print(f"{second} is the biggest number")
else:
    print(f"{first} and {second} are equal")
